sql:
SELECT name
FROM map_layers
WHERE enabled = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_accesses
FROM layer_access
WHERE layer_id = 1;

SELECT access_type, COUNT(*) AS total_access
FROM layer_access
GROUP BY access_type;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS enabled_layers_count
  FROM map_layers
  WHERE enabled = 1;

SELECT type_name
FROM layer_types
WHERE group_id = 1;

SELECT access_type
FROM layer_access
WHERE user_id = 1 AND layer_id = 0;

SELECT layer_id
FROM layer_history
WHERE change_type = 'add';

external_knowledge:
Assuming the first quartile (Q1) represents the highest 25% of layers by access and change frequencies; 
Access frequency refers to how often a layer is accessed; 
Change frequency refers to how often changes are made to a layer.
